## General Description

The **SONOZAP** **_Atomizer_** generator contains the latest advances in circuitry and software design, for
efficiently operating your atomizer nozzle.

On the front panel (Figure 1 ) is a 4 line by 20 character LCD display that is programed to provide the
operating performance of the nozzle attached, and user settings. The front panel also has a selectable
**UP DOWN** ARROWS, that gives the operator control over the power of the attached nozzle and a five
key membrane switch for programing user parameters through a **menu**. At the back of the generator
is the ON/OFF power switch, 95-265V power input, output jack to the nozzle and RS- 232
communication connector with external enable/disable pin, PLC connections and external power
control. See page 12 for DB9 pin assignments.

**Figure 1:**


**Display:**

The display provides the operator with information about the performance of the nozzle. At the top of
the display is the SONOZAPTM Atomizer name. The next line provides the power for the process.

The next line ( not shown) provides the operator with the frequency that the probe is operating at.

The next line (not shown) provides the operator with a Bar Graph for Power Level information.

## Key Pad

The key pad is made up of four keys, each key has between one and two functions, depending upon
the mode of operation.

Each Key will be described below:


**On/Off:**

The On/Off button is used to turn the power to the probe On and Off. The status of this button is
indicated on the display next to the POWER. If the display indicates “OFF”, no power is delivered to
the probe. If the display reads a POWER, the unit is on.

**Enter:**

The enter key allows access to the Configuration Menu. It displays the unit serial number with the set-
up information for the Nozzle purchased, Power Units, VMD Droplet Simulator, Cleaning and additional
operations. Pressing Up/ Down will scroll to the next item. Pressing Enter will allow adjustments to the
function selected. Pressing ON/OFF saves the results.

**Arrows:**

The arrows are used to scroll through the menu, change power and settings.

Use the arrows to select nozzle frequency and operation.

The up arrow causes the digits to scroll upwards

The down arrow causes the digits to scroll downwards or move to the next field.

Pressing On/OFF will save the results.


**Menu:**

In the default screen, display has Sonozap Atomizer and PWR:OFF

Press the enter key and the units menu items are displayed.

