## Serial Number

This is the serial number of the unit. The serial number is the date the unit was calibrated for the
customer and is representative of the date purchased. The first two characters is the month, the next
two the day, the next two the year and the last two the unit number.

**Select Probe**

Select Probe allows the user to select the nozzle that is programmed into the generator. This unit can


be programmed for up to eight nozzles, each can be selected if purchased, but only one at a time can
be operated. Use the up down arrows to select the nozzle for operation, pressing enter will select that
nozzle. When in the menu the current frequency is displayed.

## Calibrate New Probe

This feature is only used when the customer orders a new probe of the same frequency originally
purchased. Only a new probe that is identified in the **Select Probe** menu is permitted with this feature.
No other nozzle can be used with this feature. Attach new probe and follow instructions on screen to
calibrate. The user wil be instructed to turn unit off before settings are to be used.

## VMD Droplet Simulator

Allows user to fine tune a process by modifying the parameters of the solution sprayed while operating
the atomizer nozzle. Droplet size displayed when enabled, simulates the information provided to the
generator and shows size changes based on an atomizers frequency and power. The display will show
the drop size and distribution. To operate, enable in the main menu, select each parameter and
change to match solution and flow rate used. This information is inserted into our proprietary algorithm
for determining VMD droplet size and is displayed on the top line of the generators running screen in
real time when enabled. To leave menu, press **ON/OFF**. The range of viscosity is 0.10 - 500 cp,
surface tension 10. 0 - 99. 9 Dynes/cm, density. 500 - 3. 500 g/cc and flow rate. 010 - 100 ml/min.

## Cleaning

Enabling this feature will keep the atomizer nozzle clean after spraying.
In the default screen, pressing **ENTER** will bring up the user menu, scroll to **Cleaning function** in the
list and use the **UP/ DOWN** arrows to change to ON.
Select the **ENTER** key to exit to default screen.
Press the **ON/OFF** to go running. The display will read **CLEANING PROBE** , **START PUMP.** Begin
pumping cleaning solution (ie. Alcohol, MEK, Acetone, Soapy Solution).
Power to the probe will automatically adjust during the cleaning operation and will operate for one
minute. After the time expires, the generator will indicate **Process Complete** and return to the default
screen. At this point the user can clean again or enter the menu and turn feature **OFF**.

## Power Precision

The bottom of the generator has a bar graph showing the percentage of power sent to the atomizer
nozzle**.** Using the up down arrows will increase or decrease the power in 1 % increments up to 100 %.
Entering the menu and scrolling to PWR Precission allows the user to change from standard 1%
increments to fine 0. 3 - 0.5% steps or extra fine, depending on the probe and calibration configuration
performed at the factory.
**NOTE:** Extra fine mode allows the power to go down from 1% for super low flow and precision coating.

## Automatic Atomization Power Adjust (AAPA)

Auto Atomization Power Adjustment is a function that allows the atomizer nozzle to keep the tip
amplitude constant during liquid loading based on the flow rate of the liquid and the liquid parameters,
viscosity, density, surface tension, molecular structure. The function default value for this feature is on.


In the main menu the up down arrows allows selection this to be off. This is useful for very low flows
using a micro feed tubes or for coating applications. Some errors can occur if liquids parameters
cause poor operation of the atomizer nozzle. The menu will display the current condition of this feature
either on or off

## Constant Power

The constant power mode allows the user to freeze the power delivered to the probe for a process.
When freezing the power the AAPA will be overridden and the number of decimal places displayed
will be one. The generator will hold the power constant at all times even during load changes which
could have a effect on the performance. It is best to set the flow rate and conditions before freezing
the power in place. Once frozen the power will be saved even when shut off, so it can be retrieved for
the next use. To release this condition use the up/down arrows. In the menu the display will indicate
if this is on or off.

## Standard / Turbo

This mode allows the user to select the default standard or option turbo. In the standard mode the
probe will operate as in previous versions and sometimes can be too low for the solution being
atomized, like oils. With the turbo option selected, extra power is delivered to the probe for difficult
solutions. It maybe necessary to order the probe with cooling ports when using this option since the
power is higher. In the menu the mode standard or turbo operation mode is displayed.

## External Enable Pin

External Enable Pin on the DB9 connector is pin 4, controlling the status of this pin is used to turn on
and off the nozzle during atomization. This is used for interfacing the generator to other types of
equipment. The default value for this feature is for pin 4 to be open, internally high, and the atomizer
will work without a connection to this connector. Pulling this pin to ground or pin 5 will disable
atomization. If the application requires the opposite configuration, select this feature and use the up
down arrows to change the status of this pin to disable when high and enable when pulling to ground.
The menu will display the status of this feature.

## External Power Control

External power control is on the DB9 pin 1. Selecting this feature will allow the atomizer nozzle to be
controlled with a 0 -5 VDC signal, can be used with a PLC. Zero being no power and 5 VDC maximum
power. The default setting for this function is off and the generator will power the nozzle with the
up/down arrows. A pull down resistor is internal to the generator and no signal needs to be present.

## External Trigger

External trigger function is pin 9 on the DB 9. This function works with the external enable/disable (pin
4). Entering the menu a selection is provided to operate with the external enable/disable. A time delay
can be set by the user for the application. Default is OFF. Use On/OFF to change TRIGGER
sequence. Use UP/DN to change delay. Trigger is a 0 -5 VDC Output (Not a Input).

