## DB9 Pin Assignments

**NOTE: Do Not Connect to Pins Unless Used for
Function Listed Below. (DAMAGE MAY OCCUR)
Refer to semiconductor for input and output
capabilities 74AHC04.**

Pin 1: External power control, enable this feature selectable from the main menu, 0-5VDC
Pin 2: RXD Receive data for RS 232 communication, use with PC APP or user generated software control
Pin 3: TXD Transmitt data for RS 232 communication, use with PC APP or user generated control
Pin 4: External enable/disable, PLC, user configurable high or low disable or enable from main menu ,0-5VDC
Pin 5: Earth ground and ground for the entire system, needs to be connected for all DB9 functions
Pin 6 : Used when atomizer generator is operated in a system. Allows user to use a signal to enter **RUNNING** state.
Bring pin low for 250 ms and release will enter running state, 0-5VDC
Pin 7: PLC Busy signal, high busy, low not busy, 0-5 VDC
Pin 8: PLC Error signal for functional faults, high error, low no error, 0-5VDC
Pin 9: External trigger, enable/disable, configurable through main menu, 0-5VDC


