**Troubleshooting:**

If the generator when turned on exhibits a condition where two blank lines remain on the LCD screen
or the characters look gobbled the problem probably is EMI contamination, over voltage or shorting
of power supply or turning off on too rapidly.

Any error message from the generator needs to be investigated. These messages are the result of
the cable breaking, probe clogged or damaged, overheating of power drivers inside the unit.
Generator or probe needs to be repaired in these cases.

If the generator displays “ **shut unit off and attach converter** ” this is probably due to the cable
breaking the connection to the atomizer nozzle or generator. Also, this could be a broken
connection in side the nozzle. In this case the generator automatically disables power.

A message that indicates “ **Check probe frequency or probe loading** ” is the result of three
possibilities.

1. The frequency selected from the menu does not match the probe being used.
2. Something is inside the probe preventing it from vibrating. Blow out with air.
3. Power is too low and something is on the tip causing excessive loading for the power selected.

A message that indicates “ **Current Overload** ” is the result of too much power measured in the
power amplifiers.

A message that indicates “ **Check FETs** ” could be the result of the power amplifiers burned or
improper shutting down unit and turning on too quickly**.**


